    <title>Version 0.3.76</title>
    <description><![CDATA[<h2>What&#x27;s New in v0.3.76</h2>

<h3>Shared Image File Sync</h3>
<p>Shared images from iPhone now sync to your Mac as files (not just metadata). Stored at <code>phones/{device}/shared-images/{date}/</code>. Supports HEIC, JPEG, PNG, WebP, GIF — original format preserved, no re-encoding.</p>

<h3>Per-Table Sync Error Isolation</h3>
<p>A missing table on the Mac (e.g., before migration runs) no longer fails the entire sync batch. Other tables sync normally, and failed tables retry next cycle.</p>

<h3>Share Extension Fixes</h3>
<li>No more full-screen overlay — extension is invisible, dismisses instantly</li>
<li>Image sharing works: detects format from file headers, loads all UTI types</li>
<li>Swipe-to-delete in Shared Items list (removes DB row + image file)</li>

<h3>Sparkle Changelog Fix</h3>
<p>Release notes now appear in the macOS update dialog (was showing &quot;Bug fixes and improvements&quot; due to wrong auth token).</p>

<h3>CI: Raw xcodebuild</h3>
<p>Switched from <code>tuist xcodebuild</code> to raw <code>xcodebuild</code> for better DerivedData cache reuse and parallel compilation.</p>]]></description>
